<br>
For self study, I really like the Japanese for Busy People series. It's a good choice.<br>
<br>
My suggestion would be to learn the kana as soon as you can. The romaji is handy, but is a crutch that in my opinion is better left behind. The next volume has a much greater reliance on kana, so you should have the kana memorized by the time you get to it.<br>
